 class=\"tabl>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Cups, Cones &amp; Sundaes</th>\n<td>59¢ per ounce</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Quarts</th>\n<td>$7.25</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pints</th>\n<td>$4.75</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Milkshakes</th>\n<td>$6.95</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Banana Splits</th>\n<td>$7.25</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cow Pie Sundae</th>\n<td>$6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Ice Cream Cookie Sandwich</th>\n<td>$4.99</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Soda</th>\n<td>$1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Bottled Water</th>\n<td>$1.25</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Coffee</th>\n<td>$1.99</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Ice Cream Cakes</th>\n<td>6 inch $19.99\n9 inch $29.99\n¼ Sheet Cake (2 inches thick) $41.99</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cookie Cake</th>\n<td>6 inch $19.99</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Ice Cream Pies</th>\n<td>$20</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3>Ice Cream Flavors</h3>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Bacon</th>\n<td>As seen on Food Network’s “Unwrapped!”</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Black Raspberry</th>\n<td>A delightful pureed black raspberry ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Black Raspberry Chip</th>\n<td>Black raspberry ice cream with miniature chocolate chips.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Butter Brickle</th>\n<td>Butter flavored ice cream scattered with toffee pieces.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Butter Pecan</th>\n<td>A sweet buttery ice cream laced with pecan nut pieces.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cake Batter</th>\n<td>Just like licking mom’s cake bowl as a kid!</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cappuccino Crunch</th>\n<td>Cappuccino Coffee flavored ice cream with an almond toffee crunch!</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cherry Vanilla</th>\n<td>Vanilla ice cream with a generous portion of dark, sweet cherry halves.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Chocolate</th>\n<td>Creamy chocolate ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Chocolate Almond</th>\n<td>Chocolate ice cream with chips of toasted almonds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough</th>\n<td>Chocolate chip ice cream infused with pieces of chocolate chip cookie dough.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Chocolate Peanut Butter</th>\n<td>Peanut butter swirled in chocolate ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Chocolate Thunder</th>\n<td>A thunderous roar of chocolate!</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Coconut</th>\n<td>A coconut flavored ice cream with shredded coconut blended in.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Coffee</th>\n<td>Something for the coffee-holic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cookies &amp; Cream</th>\n<td>Crushed Oreo cookies in vanilla ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cotton Candy</th>\n<td>The taste of cotton candy in ice cream!</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Dirt (it’s for the kids!)</th>\n<td>Straight out of the Woodside farm fields! Gummy worms and crushed Oreo cookies give texture to chocolate ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Motor Oil</th>\n<td>Coffee ice cream with a caramel &amp; fudge swirl. (The caramel is GREEN!)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Peach</th>\n<td>A Delaware favorite! Peach slices in peach flavored ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Peanut Butter &amp; Jelly</th>\n<td>An award-winning flavor from Woodside Farm Creamery. Peanut butter and raspberry jelly to tempt your taste buds!</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Peppermint Chip</th>\n<td>Yes! It is pink!! Chocolate chips in peppermint flavored ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Rocky Road</th>\n<td>Miniature marshmallows and chocolate covered toasted almonds blended in chocolate ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Strawberry</th>\n<td>A strawberry flavored ice cream with delicious sliced strawberries throughout.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>No Sugar Added Black Raspberry</th>\n<td>A no sugar added ice cream made with pureed black raspberries.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>No Sugar Added Vanilla</th>\n<td>A no sugar added version of an American favorite.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Turtle</th>\n<td>A Woodside Farm Creamery special flavor! Toasted pecan pieces and caramel blended in chocolate ice cream.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Vanilla</th>\n<td>Everyone has it! Ours is made with fresh ground vanilla beans from around the globe.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/WoodsideCreamery/\">Follow us on Facebook</a> to be the first to know when we adjust our menu!\n<h3>Ice Cream Cakes</h3>\nWe are now offering Ice Cream Cakes in 3 different sizes. All three of our cakes consist of two layers of our homemade ice cream (chocolate and vanilla), divided by a layer of crushed Oreo, and wrapped in a delicious buttercream icing.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-93 size-medium\" src=\"http://pandora-equator-3000.codio.io/wp-content/uploads/ice-cream-cakes-300x236.jpg\" alt=\"Picture Collage of Woodside Farm Creamery’s Ice Cream Cakes\" width=\"300\" height=\"236\" />\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>6 Inch Round Ice Cream Cake (3 inches thick)</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Serves 8–10 people</li>\n 	<li>$19.99</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n 	<li><strong>9 Inch Round Ice Cream Cake (2 inches thick)</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Serves 15–18 people</li>\n 	<li>$29.99</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n 	<li><strong>¼ Sheet Ice Cream Cake (2 inches thick)</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Serves 25–30 people</li>\n 	<li>$41.99</li>\n 	<li><em>Sheet Cake is available by special order only</em></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions for Slicing</h4>\n<strong>You’ll need:</strong> Long bladed knife and a tall glass of hot/warm water.\n<ol>\n 	<li>40–45 minutes (30 minutes for a 6-inch cake) before slicing and serving your ice cream cake, transfer the cake from the freezer to the refrigerator. (This will soften the ice cream enough to be able to cut through.)</li>\n 	<li>Place the knife in the glass of warm water to heat up the blade.</li>\n 	<li>When ready to slice and serve, remove the cake from the fridge and slice down the center of the cake. *You may need to press firmly all the way down through the two layers on the first knife insertion, pull the knife straight up and back out, and then continue across the cake in sections, to make sure you slice through the entire cake.</li>\n 	<li>As you slice, you’ll need to clean off your knife in the glass of warm water making sure you wip off the excess water.</li>\n 	<li>Top each slice with a little whipped cream, and enjoy!</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Ice Cream Pies</h3>\nOur farm fresh ice cream pies are 9-inches in diameter and contain approximately a quart and a half of ice cream. They are a popular holiday treat! Ice Cream Pies are available for the Thanksgiving and Christmas holidays, as well as during the summer season (personalized flavors by special request).\n\nPies are individually packaged in a clear plastic protective pie case, and come in the following flavors:\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>Oreo Crust</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Vanilla &amp; Chocolate</li>\n 	<li>Black Raspberry &amp; Chocolate</li>\n 	<li>Peppermint &amp; Chocolate</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n 	<li><strong>Golden Graham Cracker Crust</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Pumpkin &amp; Vanilla</li>\n 	<li>Cappuccino Crunch &amp; Vanilla</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Orders for pies during the season will require seven (7) days advanced notice.</strong>\n\nPlease call us at <strong>302-239-9847</strong> for additional information and to place an order.','Menu','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-autosave-v1','','','2017-04-01 12:11:34','2017-04-01 16:11:34','',9,'http://pandora-equator-3000.codio.io/index.php/9-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(85,1,'2017-03-31 23:15:39','2017-04-01 03:15:39','<h3>Creamery Menu</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Cups, Cones &amp; Sundaes</th>\r\n<th>59¢ per ounce</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Quarts</td>\r\n<td>$7.25</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Pints</td>\r\n<td>$4.75</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Milkshakes</td>\r\n<td>$6.95</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Banana Splits</td>\r\n<td>$7.25</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cow Pie Sundae</td>\r\n<td>$6</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Ice Cream Cookie Sandwich</td>\r\n<td>$4.99</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Soda</td>\r\n<td>$1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Bottled Water</td>\r\n<td>$1.25</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Coffee</td>\r\n<td>$1.99</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Ice Cream Cakes</td>